race.comment: AMBELLO (2) doesn't win out of turn but is knocking on the door. Drawn sticky but will find this easier and only needs to hold his form to be winning. Murtagh's booking signals confidence. SACRED CHORD (5) has been mixing his form this campaign but boasts strong peaks. Should blend into the race nicely from his middle draw and be right there when they quicken. HATESCHOOLCONCERTS (9) wasn't far away last time at Ceduna and is worth keeping safe under the light weight. MR JONES (3) is drawn well for his return and has jumped out well in readiness. Expect Rawiller to have him poised to strike when they balance up. In the mix.
